                .competitive-audit__analysis
                    .analysis__tier-1  
                        %p.tier-title   
                            Tier 1 — Direct Competitors
                        .columns
                            .column
                                .analysis__card
                                    .card-top
                                        .card-label.blue
                                            %p Strongest Rival
                                        %p.card-title The Honest Kitchen
                                        %p.card-subtitle thehonestkitchen.com
                                        %p.card-text
                                            The closest competitor in positioning. Human-grade ingredients, strong educational content, and a clear brand story. Product pages lead with ingredients and feeding instructions. Their pet quiz is well-executed and reduces decision fatigue effectively.
                                    .card-takeaway
                                        %p
                                            %span Takeaway:
                                            Sets the standard for a transparent, education-first holistic pet food site. The redesign needs to match this quality while preserving Dr. Harvey's handcrafted, family-owned differentiation.
                            .column
                                .analysis__card
                                    .card-top
                                        .card-label.green
                                            %p Best Design Quality
                                        %p.card-title Open Farm
                                        %p.card-subtitle openfarmpet.com
                                        %p.card-text
                                            The most visually polished site in the competitive set. Clean, modern, premium feel with strong sourcing transparency, with each product links to the specific farm it came from. Strong sustainability narrative throughout.
                                    .card-takeaway
                                        %p
                                            %span Takeaway:
                                            Premium visual quality and sourcing specificity are not mutually exclusive with warmth. You can look polished and still communicate genuine care.
                    .analysis__tier-2 
                        %p.tier-title   
                            Tier 2 — Indirect Competitors
                        .columns
                            .column
                                .analysis__card
                                    .card-top
                                        .card-label.yellow
                                            %p Discovery UX Reference
                                        %p.card-title Chewy
                                        %p.card-subtitle chewy.com
                                        %p.card-text
                                            Excellent product filtering and discovery. Brand feels corporate but the shopping experience is smooth. Lacks meaningful educational content for first-time buyers. The brand site must offer something Chewy cannot like deeper story, preparation guidance, and a direct community relationship.
                                    .card-takeaway
                                        %p
                                            %span Takeaway:
                                            Chewy dominates discovery but cannot offer a brand relationship. The opportunity is in everything a retailer cannot do: story, education, and community.
                            .column
                                .analysis__card
                                    .card-top
                                        .card-label.pink
                                            %p Mass Market Cautionary Tale
                                        %p.card-title Blue Buffalo
                                        %p.card-subtitle bluebuffalo.com
                                        %p.card-text
                                            The most recognized name in natural pet food, now owned by General Mills. The site is polished with strong product filtering and life-stage navigation, but the corporate ownership shows. Ingredient messaging is repetitive and surface-level, and the handcrafted identity is essentially gone.
                                    .card-takeaway
                                        %p
                                            %span Takeaway:
                                            Polish increased when it scaled up but the authenticity that holistic buyers respond to got diluted. Dr. Harvey's independence is a direct competitive advantage, but only if the site communicates it clearly.
        .case-study__user-interviews
            .anchor#users
            .container
                .columns.is-variable.is-6-desktop
                    .column.is-3
                        %p.eyebrow User Research
                        %h3 Understanding users
                    .column.is-8.is-offset-1
                        %p To understand what Dr. Harvey's customers need from the site, industry research, customer feedback, and past user testing were analyzed. Four recurring themes emerged that directly shaped the design direction.
                        .case-study__interview-quotes
                            .columns.is-multiline.is-variable.is-3-desktop
                                .column.is-6
                                    .case-study-quote.green
                                        .case-study__quote-label.c1
                                            %p Clarity
                                        %p Preparation confusion is the most commonly cited friction point. Customers who love the product frequently report needing external resources like YouTube videos, forums, or direct customer service to feel confident about portions and preparation before committing to a purchase.
                                        .case-study-quote__source
                                            %p Observed across Chewy reviews, Trustpilot, and pet food forums
                                .column.is-6
                                    .case-study-quote.pink
                                        .case-study__quote-label.c2
                                            %p Emotional Connection
                                        %p Reviewers consistently describe Dr. Harvey's in personal, relationship-driven language. The founder story and family-owned identity surface repeatedly as reasons for trust. The gap between that emotional product experience and the website's ability to reflect it is a recurring theme.
                                        .case-study-quote__source
                                            %p Observed across Chewy reviews, Wag, and Hepper
                                .column.is-6
                                    .case-study-quote.blue
                                        .case-study__quote-label.c3
                                            %p Ingredients
                                        %p Ingredient quality is the primary purchase driver across reviews. Customers cite whole food ingredients, human-grade sourcing, and the absence of artificial additives as the deciding factors. When ingredient information is hard to find or buried, it stalls the decision entirely.
                                        .case-study-quote__source
                                            %p Observed across Chewy reviews, Dog Food Advisor, and Dogster
                                .column.is-6
                                    .case-study-quote.yellow
                                        .case-study__quote-label.c4
                                            %p Trust Signals
                                        %p Vet guidance comes up frequently in the context of specialized diets, kidney disease, and chronic conditions. Customers with health-specific needs actively look for professional endorsement or credentials before spending at this price point.
                                        .case-study-quote__source
                                            %p Observed across Trustpilot, Pet Health Pros, and Hepper
        .case-study__problem-statement
            .anchor#problem
            .container
                .columns
                    .column.is-3
                        %p.eyebrow Challenges
                        %h3 Problem Statement
                    .column.is-8.is-offset-1-desktop
                        %p Many shoppers do not fully understand what holistic pet food is or why it costs more than conventional options. Dr. Harvey's products are not an impulse buy but an intentional investment in a pet's long-term health, usually chosen after careful research and consideration. The challenge was to redesign the website to communicate this value clearly while keeping the brand's authentic, handcrafted feel. The site needed to make ingredient information, feeding guides, and educational content easy to find and search-friendly, helping new customers feel informed and confident. At the same time, the user experience had to support higher conversions and repeat purchases through clear, honest flows and thoughtful upsells, never resorting to pushy tactics. Finally, the mobile experience needed to be seamless, so loyal customers could easily reorder and manage their accounts anytime, anywhere.
        .case-study__main-concerns
            .anchor#concerns
            .container
                .columns
                    .column.is-3
                        %p.eyebrow Main Concerns
                        %h3 Key Challenges
                    .column.is-8.is-offset-1-desktop
                        .main-concerns__concerns-wrapper
                            %p Four recurring challenges from user research and competitive analysis shaped the design priorities for the redesign.
                            .columns.is-multiline.is-variable.is-8-desktop
                                .column.is-6
                                    .main-concerns__concerns-box
                                        .concerns-box__img-wrapper
                                            %p 📋
                                        %h4 Preparation complexity
                                        %p Dr. Harvey's products require preparation: mixing, rehydrating, portioning. Users who don't understand how to prepare the food abandon the purchase. Preparation guides need to be central to the product page experience, not an afterthought.
                                .column.is-6
                                    .main-concerns__concerns-box
                                        .concerns-box__img-wrapper
                                            %p 🤍
                                        %h4 Emotional authenticity
                                        %p The brand's handcrafted, family-owned identity is its strongest differentiator. The previous site felt generic and didn't communicate the 40-year story or the personal care behind the products. Redesigning with warmth and authenticity was a core constraint.
                                .column.is-6
                                    .main-concerns__concerns-box
                                        .concerns-box__img-wrapper
                                            %p 🔍
                                        %h4 Information overload
                                        %p Dr. Harvey's has a wide product range across multiple formats and dietary philosophies. Without clear filtering, categorization, and guided discovery, users get overwhelmed and default to familiar brands.
                                .column.is-6
                                    .main-concerns__concerns-box
                                        .concerns-box__img-wrapper
                                            %p 💰
                                        %h4 Trust at a premium price
                                        %p Dr. Harvey's products cost significantly more than conventional pet food. At that price point, every trust signal matters like vet endorsements, certifications, sourcing transparency, customer reviews.
        .case-study__project-goals
            .anchor#goals
            .container
                .columns
                    .column.is-3
                        %p.eyebrow Objectives
                        %h3 Revewing project goals
                    .column.is-8.is-offset-1
                        %p Dr. Harvey's business goals around conversions and repeat purchases aligned closely with what users needed: a site that educates, builds trust, and makes shopping feel easy and authentic. The project focused on designing toward that intersection.
